-- IPS Shares Soar as Company Wins 5-Year Contract: Zurich Mover
-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 2012-11-27T11:08:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-27/ips-shares-soar-as-company-wins-5-year-contract-zurich-mover.html
IPS Innovative Packaging Solutions
AG (IPS)  soared in Zurich trading after winning a five-year contract
for personal care products.  The shares rose 13 percent,the biggest intraday increase
since April 2010, to 9.5 francs at 12:04 local time. More than
14,000 shares exchanged hands, the most since August. IPS has
advanced 3.6 percent this year, giving it a market value of
about 94 million francs ($101 million).  “An annual quantity of several million dispensers for men
and women’s personal care products will be manufactured, filled,
labeled and dispatched from the new, fully automated
manufacturing facility of the IPS joint venture Air0lux in
Bilten, Switzerland,” according to a statement today.  IPS didn’t say how much the deal was worth or identify the
“leading retailer” who placed the order.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  